# LAMMPS Input File
# Licensed under CC BY 4.0
# A Set of Materials-Science Tutorials for the LAMMPS Simulation Package
# Modernized recreation of the MSU/CAVS tutorials by Mark A. Tschopp
# Tutorial 15, part 2 (step 2 of 2): the melting point from interface motion.
#
# Hold the two-phase cell built by coexist.lmp at a series of fixed
# temperatures.  Below T_m the solid grows and consumes the liquid; above
# T_m it melts.  The crystalline fraction is read from the INHERENT STRUCTURE
# (a brief energy minimization removes thermal noise) because near T_m the
# instantaneous structures of hot solid and liquid overlap too much for
# common-neighbor analysis to separate them.  fcc fraction vs T falls through
# one half at T_m.
#
# This is a deliberately SHORT scan (small cell, few temperatures, short
# runs) so it finishes in minutes on a laptop.  It locates T_m only roughly;
# a converged value needs a larger cell, more temperatures, and longer runs
# -- and a parallel machine.  See the note in the tutorial text.

variable T index 900 925 950 975          # temperatures to scan (K)
label loop
clear
